        <div class="allergy_table">
          <h4>Learn More About Common Allergens and How to Avoid Them</h4>
          <table>
              <thead>
                  <tr>
                      <th>Allergen</th>
                      <th>Source</th>
                      <th>How to Avoid</th>
                  </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                  <tr>
                      <td>Pollen</td>
                      <td>Trees, grasses, and weeds</td>
                      <td>Stay indoors during peak pollen seasons, keep windows closed, use air filters.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                      <td>Dust Mites</td>
                      <td>Household dust</td>
                      <td>Wash bedding in hot water, use dust mite-proof covers, vacuum regularly.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                      <td>Pet Dander</td>
                      <td>Skin flakes, saliva, and urine of animals</td>
                      <td>Keep pets out of bedrooms, bathe pets regularly, use HEPA filters.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                      <td>Mold</td>
                      <td>Damp areas such as bathrooms and basements</td>
                      <td>Reduce indoor humidity, fix leaks, clean moldy surfaces with disinfectants.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                      <td>Food Allergens</td>
                      <td>Peanuts, shellfish, dairy, etc.</td>
                      <td>Read food labels, avoid cross-contamination, carry emergency medication.</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                      <td>Insect Stings</td>
                      <td>Bees, wasps, fire ants</td>
                      <td>Avoid areas with nests, wear protective clothing, carry epinephrine if allergic.</td>
                  </tr>
              </tbody>
          </table>
